#Approach:

Find First and Last Position in Sorted Array – Binary Search Approach

Is problem me hume sorted array me target ka first index aur last index find karna hota hai.
Isliye hum simple binary search ka modified version use karte hain.

First Occurrence:
Binary search lagao.
Agar nums[mid] == target:
    ans = mid store karo
    Left side me search karo (high = mid - 1)
Kyuki hume aur pehla occurrence mil sakta hai.

Agar nums[mid] < target:
    Right side me jao (low = mid + 1)
Agar nums[mid] > target:
    Left side me jao (high = mid - 1)

Last Occurrence:
Binary search lagao.
Agar nums[mid] == target:
    ans = mid store karo
    Right side me search karo (low = mid + 1)
Kyuki hume aur last occurrence mil sakta hai.

Baaki conditions same rahengi.

Agar target nahi milta to ans -1 rahega.

Time Complexity: O(log n)

Count Occurrences in Sorted Array

Count = lastOccurence - firstOccurence + 1

Agar firstOccurence = -1 ho,
to count = 0 (element exist hi nahi karta).

Memory Trick:
First Occ → left jao
Last Occ → right jao
Count = last - first + 1


#Code:

class Solution {

    public int firstOcc(int[] nums, int target){
        //First Occurence
        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;
        int ans = -1;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;

            if(nums[mid] == target){
                ans = mid;
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else if(nums[mid] < target){
                low = mid+1;
            }
            else{
                high = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public int lastOcc(int[] nums, int target){
        //Last Occurence
        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;
        int ans = -1;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;

            if(nums[mid] == target){
                ans = mid;
                low = mid+1;
            }
            else if(nums[mid] > target){
                high = mid-1;
            }
            else{
                low = mid+1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public int[] searchRange(int[] nums, int target) {
        int val1 = firstOcc(nums, target);
        int val2 = lastOcc(nums, target);

        int[] result = {val1, val2};
        return result;
    }
}
